                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.7961/36: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-14T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 14, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>318. Department’s 317, September 14, 3 p.m. The Department wishes you to know for
                    your own information but not for communication to the Japanese Government that
                    Pan American Airways has informed the Department that when weather conditions
                    make it doubtful whether its planes could be sure of following the suggested
                    route in and out of Macao, the scheduled stop at Macao will be omitted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
